                <h3>
                    Why are elderly women at high risk of homelessness when they suffer from family violence?
                </h3>
                <p class="font-italic">
                    According to the government
                    report, in Australia, the
                    number of older women
                    accessing homelessness
                    services is increasing. In
                    2017–18 over 13,800 older
                    women accessed specialist
                    homeless services, a 63%
                    increase in five years.
                </p>
                <p>
                    The main reasons older women seek
                    assistance often relate to domestic and family violence, housing
                    issues and financial difficulties
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>

